ResponseBody.displayName: .NET Mgmt SDK Test with TTL = 1 Day

properties.title: Apt-Get
properties.description: Install Apt packages on Linux using the apt-get utility. This system is the default package manager installed on Debian and Debian-based distributions such as Ubuntu.

packages.description: The packages to install on the VM, separated by spaces. All of the package declarations supported by apt-get are supported here as well, see http://manpages.debian.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=apt-get for an in-depth look at the package specifications available.

update.description: Run apt-get update prior to running the full install command. Allowed values are 'true' and 'false'. Note that no additional options are passed to the 'apt-get update' command other than --quiet --assume-yes. It is recommended for you to set this to true and run update.

options.description: Any additional options to pass to the apt-get command line. These options will precede the install command when executed. Please see http://manpages.debian.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=apt-get for an in-depth look at the options available. Note that --assume-yes and --quiet are always passed automatically.

properties.title: Chef Client
properties.description: Downloads and installs the client, registers with the specified Chef server, does an initial checkin, and applies any recipes in the run list.

chefNodeName.description: The name to assign to this VM as used by the Chef server. A node is any computer that is managed by a Chef server.

chefServerUrl.description: The URL for the Chef server. For example: https://api.chef.io/organizations/myorgname

validationClientName.description: The name of the validator key that is used by the client to access the Chef server during the initial client run. For example: myorgname-validator

validationKey.description: The file containing the validation private key for the organization.  For example: myorgname-validator.pem

clientRb.description: Configuration file for chef-client, should not contain values that replicate other parameters seen here

sslVerifyMode.description: SSL peer verification during the chef-client run to the Chef server.  Permitted values are 'none' and 'peer'.  Default is 'peer'.

properties.title: Reset VM Password
properties.description: Uses the VMAccess extension to reset the built-in administrator account.

password.description: New password for the user name

metadata.description: Whether or not reset the ssh.

properties.title: Reset VM SSH Key
properties.description: Uses the VMAccess extension to reset the built-in administrator account.

metadata.description: Whether or not reset the ssh.

properties.title: Deploy App from Azure Storage
properties.description: Deploy an app stored in an Azure container to Linux

container.description: The name of the Azure container to deploy.

storageConnectionString.description: The connection string to the Azure storage account container containing the app.

destination.description: The destination folder on the VM to deploy the app.

deployScript.description: The file name of a script included in the container that will run after all files are downloaded from the container. The file path is a relative path to the script file as stored in the storage container.  E.g. myscript.sh or mysubfolder/myscript.sh

properties.title: de-provision
properties.description: Uses the Microsoft Azure Linux Agent (waagent) to de-provision a Linux VM for saving as an image.  This artifact does not work on the Core OS or FreeBSD flavors of Linux.

properties.title: Docker Container
properties.description: Install a Docker container on Linux

name.description: The name of the container, for example: MyMongo

dockerOptions.description: Additional options that affect the way in which Docker starts the container, for example: -p 27017:27017.

image.description: The name of the Docker image to be installed, for example: Jenkins, from Docker Hub.

imageArguments.description: Any additional command-line arguments that apply to the container during bootstrap, for example: --smallfiles or --storageEngine wiredTiger.

properties.title: Docker Community Edition
properties.description: Install Docker CE on Linux. -- NOTE: Docker CE will not install in RHEL, as RHEL is only supported by Docker EE. Check https://store.docker.com for information on Docker EE.

properties.description: Install Java Development Kit on Debian-based and Red Hat based distributions.

properties.title: Mono Runtime

properties.title: NPM Package
properties.description: Install NPM packages on Linux using the Node Package Manager.

installLocation.description: The local path to install the package to or the keyword 'global' to install the package(s) globally instead.

packages.description: The package names you wish to have installed via NPM separated by spaces. You can find NPM package names in the index found at https://www.npmjs.com. All npm install commands are supported, however if a Git/bitbucket/gist scope is given then you must have installed the Git artifact prior to this NPM package artifact.

otherOptions.description: Any additional options you wish to supply on the command line. See NPM install man page here: https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/install

properties.title: PowerShell on Linux
properties.description: Installs PowerShell on Linux either on CentOS 7 or Ubuntu 14.04 or 16.04 LTS.

packageUrl.description: The PowerShell on Linux package URL based on the distribution type. The supported list of distributions and URLs are available at https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell#get-powershell

properties.title: Run Bash
properties.description: Download and run a bash script

scriptFileUris.description: File(s) to download to VM for execution

skipDos2Unix.description: Skip the script conversion from MSDOS to Unix line ending

properties.title: Secure MariaDB
properties.description: Secure MariaDB instance on Linux based on mysql_secure_installation

password.description: The new root password which is set for MariaDB instance

properties.title: Swap File
properties.description: Configure swap file on Linux

size.description: The size of the swap file. Defaults to bytes, or use the suffixes K, M, or G which correspond to KiB, MiB, and GiB respectively. For example: 5G = 5 GiB, 100M = 100 MiB.

properties.title: Azure Pipelines Agent for Linux
properties.description: Downloads and installs the Azure Pipelines agent, registers with the specified Azure DevOps Services account, and adds the VM to the specified agent pool.

adoAccount.description: The name of the Azure DevOps organization to add the agent to. This is the value in your Azure DevOps URL: e.g. 'myorg' in https://dev.azure.com/myorg.

adoPat.description: A personal access token with permissions to add agents. It will only be used to register the agent. See https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/devops/pipelines/agents/v2-linux?view=azure-devops for more information

adoPool.description: The agent pool this build agent should be added to.

agentPath.description: Path where agent is stored. Any storage space used by the agent is in a subdirectory of the agent path.

agentName.description: A unique name identifying this agent. If not specified, it defaults to the hostname of the machine running the agent

properties.title: YUM Package
properties.description: Install YUM packages on Linux

packages.description: The packages to install on the VM, separated by spaces. All of the package declarations supported by YUM are supported here as well. See http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man8/yum.8.html for an in-depth look at the package specifications available.

update.description: Run YUM update prior to running the full install command. Allowed values are 'true' and 'false'. Note that no additional options are passed to the update command.

options.description: Any additional options to pass to the YUM command-line. These options will precede the install command when executed. Please see http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man8/yum.8.html for an in-depth look at the options available. Note that --assumeyes and --quiet are always passed automatically.

properties.description: Adds the given Active Directory (AD) account to the local Administrators group of the target virtual machine. The virtual machine must already be joined to the same domain as the AD account before this artifact is run.

domainJoinUsername.description: The Active Directory (AD) account (e.g. CORP\user or user@corp.contoso.com) that will be added to the local Administrators group of the target virtual machine.

installUsername.description: User with admin rights to install Atom

properties.title: AWS Command Line Interface
properties.description: Installs AWS Command Line Interface using the Chocolatey package manager

properties.title: Azure Pipelines Agent(s)
properties.description: Downloads latest Azure Pipelines agent for the account, and installs the specified number instances of the agents inside one Windows VM. Registers the agent with the Azure DevOps account, and adds agents to the specified agent pool. Note - If the specified agent folder already exists it will be overwritten.

Account.description: The name of the Azure DevOps account to add the build agent to. This is the value in your Azure DevOps URL: e.g. 'myaccount' in https://dev.azure.com/myaccount.

PersonalAccessToken.description: A personal access token with permissions to add build agents. It will only be used to register the agent.

AgentName.description: The name to give to the agent, as seen by Azure DevOps. If empty, the computer name will be used.

AgentNamePrefix.description: Prefixes every agent with string specified here.

PoolName.description: The agent pool this build agent should be added to.

AgentCount.description: The number of agents to install and add to the pool. Each agent will be named as prefix-agentname-(1..n).

Overwrite.displayName: Overwrite if agent with same name exists
Overwrite.description: If the folder with the agent name already exists, and this is true, the agent will be overwritten, otherwise installation will fail.

properties.title: Azure PowerShell
properties.description: Installs the latest version of Windows Azure PowerShell. NOTE: Requires PowerShell 5.0+ and a restart before applying. This artifact may also require a reboot after completion. Review the artifacts results for instructions.

properties.title: Beyond Compare
properties.description: Installs Beyond Compare using the Chocolatey package manager.

properties.title: Chef Client
properties.description: Downloads and installs the client, registers with the specified Chef server, does an initial checkin, and applies any recipes in the run list.

chefNodeName.description: The name to assign to this VM as used by the Chef server. A node is any computer that is managed by a Chef server.

chefServerUrl.description: The URL for the Chef server. For example: https://api.chef.io/organizations/myorgname

validationClientName.description: The name of the validator key that is used by the client to access the Chef server during the initial client run. For example: myorgname-validator

validationKey.description: The file containing the validation private key for the organization.  For example: myorgname-validator.pem

clientRb.description: Configuration file for chef-client, should not contain values that replicate other parameters seen here

sslVerifyMode.description: SSL peer verification during the chef-client run to the Chef server.  Permitted values are 'none' and 'peer'.  Default is 'peer'.

properties.title: Install Certificate from Azure Key Vault
properties.description: Installs a certificate stored in Azure Key Vault.

vaultName.description: Name of the Azure Key Vault

secretName.description: Name of the secret within the Azure Key Vault

azureServicePrincipalClientId.description: The client Id of the Service Principal used to access Azure

azureServicePrincipalKey.description: The key of the Azure Service Principal

azureServicePrincipalTenantId.description: The tenant Id of the Azure Service Principal

certificatePasswordSecretName.description: The name of the secret in the vault that contains the password to the certificate

properties.title: Reset VM Password
properties.description: Uses the VMAccess extension to reset the built-in administrator account and reset the Remote Desktop service configuration.

password.description: New password for the user name

properties.title: Install Chocolatey Packages
properties.description: Installs the Chocolatey package manager along with a user selected set of packages

packages.description: Space-, comma- or semicolon-delimited list of package names to be installed, for example: 7Zip,Fiddler4. A complete list of public packages can be found at https://chocolatey.org/packages.

allowEmptyChecksums.description: Should packages with empty checksums be allowed to be installed? This defaults to true to avoid breaking the behavior of past versions of this artifact and to ease the use of non https sources such as http/ftp, but allowing empty checksums is not recommended by chocolatey (see https://chocolatey.org/docs/commandsupgrade)

ignoreChecksums.description: Should packages that don't match their checksums be allowed to be installed? Setting this to true is not recommended by chocolatey (see https://github.com/chocolatey/choco/issues/112), but may be necessary if you have a dependency on a community maintained package that does not update its checksum to match a software provider's upgrade in a timely manner.

properties.title: Register Chocolatey Feed
properties.description: Registers a new Chocolatey package feed.

feedName.description: The name of the new feed.

feedUrl.description: The URL of the new feed. Caution - chocolatey requires a v2 service endpoint.

feedUsername.description: Username to use for authenticated feeds.

feedPassword.description: Password to use for authenticated feeds.

properties.title: Chrome
properties.description: Installs Chrome using the Chocolatey package manager

properties.title: Clone a git repository
properties.description: Installs git and clones specified repository

GitRepoURI.description: The URI of the Git repository to clone (Only HTTPS urls are supported).

Destination.description: A parent directory into which your repository will be cloned. E.g. - If you specify your destination as c:\Repos, then a new sub-directory (c:\Repos\{your local repo}) will be created and your repo will be cloned into it.

Branch.description: The branch or tag that will be checked out. Specify 'master' if you're not sure.

PersonalAccessToken.description: Personal Access Token for accessing the Git repository.

properties.title: Create web shortcut
properties.description: Creates a shortcut to a URL in the public desktop folder.

ShortcutName.description: The name to assign to the shortcut file.

ShortcutTargetPath.description: The URL that'll be invoked by this shortcut. Please ensure that the string is url-encoded.

properties.title: Azure Pipelines Deployment Group Agent
properties.description: Downloads the latest deployment agent from Azure DevOps and configures it against the specified deployment group.

accountUrl.description: The URL for the Azure DevOps account, e.g. 'myorg' in https://dev.azure.com/myorg.

projectName.description: The Azure DevOps project name, eg MyFirstProject.

deploymentGroupName.description: Name of the deployment group against which the agent has to be configured.

PersonalAccessToken.description: Personal Access Token for downloading and configuring Azure Pipelines deployment group agent.

deploymentAgentTags.description: Optionally provide comma separated list of tags for deployment agent. Example Web, DB.

agentName.description: Optionally provide agent name. Defaults to $env:COMPUTERNAME.

RunAsAutoLogon.description:
Enable autologon to run the build agent in interactive mode that can sustain machine reboots.
Set this to true if the agents will be used to run UI tests.

windowsLogonAccount.description:
The Windows logon account which will run the agent.
When autologon is enabled, agent runs as a process in the context of the specified user.

windowsLogonPassword.description: The Windows logon account password which will run the agent. This is not required for the default NT AUTHORITY\NetworkService account when running as a service.

properties.title: PowerShell Desired State Configuration Registrar - Azure Automation
properties.description: Applies a PowerShell DSC node configuration from an Azure Automation account to the specified VM.

registrationUrl.description: The URL of the Azure Automation account.  The account must exist in the same subscription as the lab.

registrationKey.description: The registration key of the Azure Automation account.  The account must exist in the same subscription as the lab.

configurationName.description: The name of the DSC Node Configuration, i.e. 'IIS.localhost'.

configurationMode.description: How the DSC configuration should be applied

configurationFrequency.description: Number of minutes between configuration sweeps

refreshFrequency.description: Number of minutes between refresh intervals

rebootIfNeeded.description: Reboots the VM if required during configuration

actionAfterReboot.description: Action to take once machine is rebooted

allowModuleOverwrite.description: Allows for overwriting the module if needed

properties.title: Self Signed Certificate
properties.description: Installs a self signed certificate for use with development

dnsName.description: DNS to bind the certificate to i.e. *.localdev.com

properties.title: Docker
properties.description: Activate Windows Container support on Windows 10 / Windows Server 2016 VMs. In addition Docker for Windows is installed if the VM supports nested virtualization (Dv3 and Ev3 size).

properties.title: Join Active Directory (AD) domain
properties.description: Joins the virtual machine to the given Active Directory domain and reboots the machine.

domainAdminUsername.description: The Active Directory (AD) account (e.g. CORP\user or user@corp.contoso.com) that has permissions to join the domain

domainAdminPassword.description: The password for the domain join user account.

domainToJoin.description: The name of the Active Directory (AD) domain to join (e.g. corp.contoso.com).

ouPath.description: Optional. Only required if you have configured organizational units in your domain; leave blank otherwise. For example, OU=Workstations,OU=Machines,DC=corp,DC=contoso,DC=com. Where 'Workstations' and 'Machines' are 2 organizational units configured in your domain.

properties.title: [Deprecated] Active Directory Domain Join
properties.description: This artifact is deprecated, please use the "Join domain and add user to local administrators group" instead. Joins a Windows VM to an Active Directory Domain. Requires that the Windows operating system can resolve the domain name and domain controller via DNS.

domainName.description: The name of the Active Directory Domain to join (e.g. "corp.contoso.com").

domainOU.description: The distinguished name of the Organizational Unit to join (e.g. "OU=DevTest,DC=corp,DC=contoso,DC=com")

domainJoinUser.description: The user account with rights to join the system to the domain (e.g. "CORP\user" or "user@corp.contoso.com")

domainJoinUserPassword.description: Password of the Domain Join User Account.

domainJoinOptions.description: Set of bit flags that define the join options. Default value of 3 is a combination of NETSETUP_JOIN_DOMAIN (0x00000001) & NETSETUP_ACCT_CREATE (0x00000002) i.e. will join the domain and create the account on the domain. For more information see https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa392154(v=vs.85).aspx

The application is installed to the default location and should show up in the recently installed list for all users on the VM (depending on the quantity of software being installed prior to logging in). Vim is not installed in such a way as to be made available on the system path.

VimInstallerPath.description: The full path to the installer file on the local VM. This should be a full path specification including the file name itself.

properties.description: Installs a certificate in the LocalMachine/My store.

certificateName.description: The name of the certificate which must be installed. This property is used to distinguish multiple instances of this artifact.

base64cert.description: Base64 encoding of the PFX certificate file. You can use the following PowerShell script to obtain a Base64-encoded representation of a certificate:",      [ "System.Convert" ],       "ToBase64String(" [ "System.IO.File" ],      "ReadAllBytes("C:\path\to\certificate.pfx"))

certificatePassword.description: The password of the certificate. It is only used to install it to the LocalMachine/My store.

properties.title: Test Parameter Types
properties.description: Template to test supported artifact parameter types.

stringParam.description: Any text string is allowed, including spaces.

securestringParam.description: Any text string is allowed, including spaces, and will be presented in UI as masked characters.

boolParam.description: Only valid boolean values are allowed (i.e. true, false, 0, 1).

selectParam.description: Only a selection from the list is allowed.

arrayParam.description: To specify multiple values, format them as a JSON array (e.g. ["item1", "item2"]).

objectParam.description: To specify multiple properties, format them as a JSON object (e.g. { prop1: "value1", prop2: "value2" }).

DesktopIcon.description: Shows VS Code icon on the Desktop

properties.title: Azure Pipelines Agent
properties.description: Downloads and installs the Azure Pipelines agent, registers with the specified Azure DevOps Services account, and adds the VM to the specified agent pool.

vstsAccount.description: The name of the Azure DevOps organization to add the agent to. This is the value in your Azure DevOps URL: e.g. 'myorg' in https://dev.azure.com/myorg.

vstsPassword.description: A personal access token with permissions to add agents. It will only be used to register the agent.

agentName.description: The name to give to the agent, as seen by Azure Pipelines. If empty, the computer name will be used.

agentNameSuffix.description: Used to identify multiple build agents on a single machine. Useful if Agent Name is defaulted to computer name.

poolName.description: The agent pool this build agent should be added to.

RunAsAutoLogon.description:
Enable autologon to run the agent in interactive mode that can sustain machine reboots.
Set this to true if the agents will be used to run UI tests.

windowsLogonAccount.description:
The Windows logon account which will run the agent.
When autologon is enabled, agent runs as a process in the context of the specified user.

windowsLogonPassword.description: The Windows logon account password which will run the agent. This is not required for the default NT AUTHORITY\NetworkService account when running as a service.

driveLetter.description: The drive letter to install the build agent to. The specified drive must already exist.

workDirectory.description: Work directory where job data is stored. Defaults to _work under the root of the agent directory. Work directory is owned by a given agent and should not be shared between multiple agents.

replaceAgent.description: Replace the agent in a pool. If another agent is listening by that name, it will start failing with a conflict.

properties.title: Download Azure Pipelines Artifact and Run Script
properties.description: Downloads the latest artifact for a given Azure Pipelines build and then executes a script from that drop.  The download will be in c:\<build pipeline name>\

vstsProjectUri.description: The URL for the Azure DevOps project that contains the build, eg https://dev.azure.com/orgname/projectName

buildDefinitionName.description: Name of the Azure DevOps Build Pipeline to be retrieved

personalAccessToken.description: Personal Access Token for accessing Azure DevOps

pathToScript.description: Path to Script for execution, eg 'drop\bin\Debug\scriptName.ps1'

scriptArguments.description: Optional arguments for the script, eg '-server localhost'

properties.title: WebDeploy
properties.description: Installs WebDeploy using the Chocolatey package manager.

properties.title: Configure WinRM
properties.description: Configures WinRM on the virtual machine. If using "Shared IP address" for your Lab VM, you will need to also add a NAT rule on the Load Balancer to allow traffic through. Alternatively, use "Public IP address" instead.

hostName.description: Specifies the FQDN of the machine or domain.

properties.title: Windows WSL
properties.description: Enables the WSL Windows feature

properties.title: Apt-Get
properties.description: Install Apt packages on Linux using the apt-get utility. This system is the default package manager installed on Debian and Debian-based distributions such as Ubuntu.

packages.description: The packages to install on the VM, separated by spaces. All of the package declarations supported by apt-get are supported here as well, see http://manpages.debian.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=apt-get for an in-depth look at the package specifications available.

update.description: Run apt-get update prior to running the full install command. Allowed values are 'true' and 'false'. Note that no additional options are passed to the 'apt-get update' command other than --quiet --assume-yes. It is recommended for you to set this to true and run update.

options.description: Any additional options to pass to the apt-get command line. These options will precede the install command when executed. Please see http://manpages.debian.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=apt-get for an in-depth look at the options available. Note that --assume-yes and --quiet are always passed automatically.
